Below is a step‐by‐step breakdown of how to recreate the target structure:

1) Main Image Analysis  
   • Block Count & Layers:  
     – There are 3 total blocks in the structure.  
     – They are arranged in 2 layers: the bottom layer has two red blocks side by side, and the top layer has one blue cube.  
   • Spatial Relationships:  
     – The two red “U”‐shaped pieces lie on the ground next to one another with their curved cutouts facing inward.  
     – The single blue cube sits centered above where the two red pieces meet.

2) Dictionary Block Selection  
   • Required Blocks:  
     – Red left “U”‐shaped block: index 3  
     – Red right “U”‐shaped block: index 4  
     – Blue cube: index 9  
   • Matching Justification:  
     – Blocks 3 and 4 are the only red pieces in the dictionary that have a horizontally oriented semicircular notch on top, matching the bottom layer.  
     – Block 9 is the blue cube and precisely matches the cube on top in the target image.

3) Assembly Order  
Use the following sequence to place the blocks (no rotations allowed beyond what’s shown in the dictionary):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 3  
  Step2: Move block with index 4  
  Step3: Move block with index 9  
}
